# CoE Infrastructure Deployment - AWS

## Description
Specialized skill for deploying **CoE Staging and Production environments** on AWS using Terraform. Follows standardized patterns with auto-configured management nodes and customizable app nodes.

**Key Features:**
- Opinionated CoE infrastructure patterns (Management + App nodes + RDS + S3 + ECR)
- Auto-configures management node (t4g.medium, 2cpu/4gb)
- Supports k3s node identification for production
- Enforces naming convention: `<project>-<type>-<env>`
- Creates isolated project folders in `projects/<project-name>/`

## CoE Infrastructure Patterns

### Staging/Non-Production
**Always Includes:**
- 1 Management Node (t4g.medium) - auto-configured
- x App Nodes (count and type based on requirements)
- 1 RDS Database (Postgres/MySQL, t-class)
- 1 S3 Bucket
- Optional Lambda functions

**Naming:** `<project>-<type>-staging` (e.g., coe-api-mgmt-node-staging)

### Production
**Always Includes:**
- 1 Management Node (t4g.medium) - auto-configured
- x App Nodes - mix of k3s and regular nodes
- 1 RDS Database (Postgres/MySQL, t-class, Multi-AZ option)
- 1 S3 Bucket
- 1 ECR Repository
- Optional Lambda functions

**Naming:** `<project>-<type>-production` (e.g., coe-api-k3s-node-1-production)

